  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is advice to a man at age 33 who failed at business and earning money, and who still lives with family?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry to hear that you're going through a tough time. It's important to remember that setbacks are a part of life's journey, and many successful people have faced similar challenges before finding their path. Here are some steps you might consider to help navigate this period:\n\n1. **Reflect on Past Experiences:**\n   - **Identify Lessons Learned:** Take some time to analyze what didn't work in your business ventures. Understanding the reasons behind the failures can provide valuable insights for future endeavors.\n   - **Assess Strengths and Weaknesses:** Recognize your skills and areas where you might need improvement. This self-awareness can guide your next steps.\n\n2. **Seek Professional Guidance:**\n   - **Career Counseling:** A professional counselor can help you explore different career options and set achievable goals.\n   - **Financial Advice:** Consulting with a financial advisor can assist you in managing your finances more effectively and planning for the future.\n\n3. **Enhance Your Skills:**\n   - **Education and Training:** Consider taking courses or attending workshops to acquire new skills or enhance existing ones. This can make you more competitive in the job market.\n   - **Certifications:** Earning relevant certifications can open up new opportunities and demonstrate your commitment to growth.\n\n4. **Explore New Opportunities:**\n   - **Job Search:** Look for job opportunities that align with your skills and interests. Don't hesitate to apply for positions even if you feel underqualified; often, employers value potential and willingness to learn.\n   - **Entrepreneurship:** If you still have a passion for business, consider starting small or exploring different industries that may better suit your strengths.\n\n5. **Build a Support Network:**\n   - **Connect with Others:** Surround yourself with supportive friends, family, or mentors who can provide encouragement and advice.\n   - **Join Communities:** Engaging with professional or interest-based groups can offer networking opportunities and a sense of camaraderie.\n\n6. **Focus on Well-being:**\n   - **Mental Health:** Experiencing failure can take a toll on your mental health. Don't hesitate to seek support from a therapist or counselor if you're feeling overwhelmed.\n   - **Physical Health:** Maintaining a healthy lifestyle through exercise, proper nutrition, and adequate rest can improve your overall well-being and resilience.\n\n7. **Set Realistic Goals:**\n   - **Short-Term Goals:** Establish achievable short-term objectives to create a sense of progress and accomplishment.\n   - **Long-Term Vision:** Develop a clear long-term plan that outlines where you want to be in the future, helping you stay focused and motivated.\n\n8. **Embrace Patience and Persistence:**\n   - **Stay Positive:** Maintaining a positive outlook can help you navigate challenges more effectively.\n   - **Be Persistent:** Success often requires time and perseverance. Keep pushing forward, even when progress seems slow.\n\nRemember, it's never too late to make changes and pursue new opportunities. Surround yourself with supportive people, stay committed to your personal growth, and be kind to yourself during this journey. Your current situation doesn't define your future, and with determination and the right strategies, you can create a path toward fulfillment and success.",
